Question: An array A consists of n integers in locations A[0], A[1] ....A[n-1]. It is required to shift the elements of the array cyclically to the left by k places, where 1 <= k <= (n-1). An incomplete algorithm for doing this in linear time, without using another array is given below. Complete the algorithm by filling in the blanks. Assume alt the variables are suitably declared., min = n; i = 0;

while (___________) { 

     temp = A[i]; j = i;

     while (________) {

     A[j] = ________ 

     j= (j + k) mod n ;

     If ( j< min ) then

         min = j;

}

A[(n + i — k) mod n] = _________

i = __________
Code: 
Choices:
A) i > min; j!= (n+i)mod n; A[j + k]; temp; i + 1 ;
B) i < min; j!= (n+i)mod n; A[j + k]; temp; i + 1;
C) i > min; j!= (n+i+k)mod n; A[(j + k)]; temp; i + 1;
D) i < min; j!= (n+i-k)mod n; A[(j + k)mod n]; temp; i + 1;
Answer: D

