Question: The following  function takes a single-linked list of integers as a parameter and rearranges the elements of the list. The function is called with the list containing the integers 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7 in the given order. What will be the contents of the list after the function completes execution? , class Node {
public:
    int value;
    Node* next;
};

void rearrange(Node* list) {
    Node* p;
    Node* q;
    int temp;
    if (list == nullptr || list->next == nullptr) {
        return;
    }
    p = list;
    q = list->next;
    while (q != nullptr) {
        temp = p->value;
        p->value = q->value;
        q->value = temp;
        p = q->next;
        q = (p != nullptr) ? p->next : nullptr;
    }
}
Code: 
Choices:
A) 1,2,3,4,5,6,7
B) 2,1,4,3,6,5,7
C) 1,3,2,5,4,7,6
D) 2,3,4,5,6,7,1
Answer: B

