C) (b). maximum : n-1 for all distinct elements, minimum: 0 for all same elements.
D) (C). j keeps count of distinct nodes in the list.
E) (a). n times, since comparison is pairwise for n elements.\n(b). maximum : n-1 for all distinct elements, minimum: 0 for all same elements.\n(C). j keeps count of distinct nodes in the list.
F) (a). n times, since comparison is pairwise for n elements.
G) (b). maximum : n-1 for all distinct elements, minimum: 0 for all same elements.
H) (C). j keeps count of distinct nodes in the list.
I) (a). n-1 times, since comparison is pairwise for n elements.\n(b). maximum : n-1 for all distinct elements, minimum: 1 for all same elements.\n(C). j keeps count of distinct nodes in the list.
J) (a). n-1 times, since comparison is pairwise for n elements.
K) (b). maximum : n-1 for all distinct elements, minimum: 1 for all same elements.
